\begin_layout Abstract
The contribution introduces a Bernoulli-like random walk with transition
 probabilities depending of its recent steps, thus implicitly depending
 on the entire walk history.
 The main objective is its application to modeling and then to prediction
 of tennis matches.
 The model is applied and tested on the tennis men Grand Slam tennis matches
 since 2009.
 The flexibility of the model is tested thoroughly on several datasets and
 the results are presented.
 It is shown that the model correctly describes the majority of all matches.
 Finally, the model is also used for the in-play real life betting with
 rather encouraging results.
\end_layout

