\begin_layout Standard
In the present paper, a model of Bernoulli-like random walk with transitions
 dependent on the walk history was introduced.
 A number of variations of this model was described by the authors in a
 recent study 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
cite{ja2019apmat}
\end_layout

\end_inset

.
 This paper shows that even the rather simple version presented here shows
 sufficient flexibility and can be applied to tennis matches modeling.
 The model was first tested statistically on historical data and the optimal
 model parameters were computed using numerical methods.
 The results were then tested in real 
\emph on
in-play 
\emph default
betting against a commercial bookmaker with rather encouraging results.
 This show a huge potential of the model being able to describe even the
 most complicated real life discrete random processes with memory.
 The application of the model on different real life problems will be subject
 of further research.
